# Local build output of the tools module. These live here, anchored with a
# leading slash, rather than as `tools/<name>` in the root .gitignore.
#
# Why: ripgrep matches a root-level pattern like `tools/llz` against the
# DIRECTORY `tools/cmd/llz`, pruning the entire llz CLI source tree (~290 files)
# from every rg search scoped to tools/. git was unaffected, so the blind spot
# was silent — it made live symbols in cmd/llz look dead to any grep-based
# audit. No pattern spelling avoids it (leading-slash anchoring, `!` negation,
# and character classes were all tested); only moving the rule into this
# directory-scoped file does, because `/llz` here cannot match `cmd/llz`.
#
# Keep new tools-module artifacts in THIS file, anchored, for the same reason —
# a root-level `tools/firewall-cidrs` would hide a future `cmd/firewall-cidrs`.
/llz
/firewall-cidrs
/firewall-controller/firewall-controller
/linode-cred-audit
/bin/
